{"parentUuid":"4353ab6c-f0aa-49aa-9979-a0f35dd64669","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afea30d80e01a0a81","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01HeP38yPBe4cDvpUhoV38Yr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"asm_metrics\":{\"vsetvli_lines\":[45],\"lmul_sew_observed\":\"e32,m1,ta,ma (VLmax=32 f32)\",\"vector_op_count\":65,\"vector_load_count\":4,\"vector_store_count\":8,\"fma_count\":24,\"vector_add_count\":8,\"load_to_compute_ratio\":\"29 scalar flw + 4 vle : 24 vfmacc (~1.4:1 scalar-flw-to-FMA)\",\"spill_lines\":[],\"scalar_memop_count\":29,\"control_flow_count\":37,\"function_line_span\":\"7-259\"},\"hypothesis\":{\"metric_issue\":\"The innermost loop body (lines 101-157) interleaves ~15 scalar flw broadcasts of filter weights (lines 104-119, 123-126, 131-135) with only 3 unique vle32.v inputs (lines 102, 127, 142) feeding 24 vfmacc.vf ops that accumulate into 8 parallel output vectors (v10-v17). The filter broadcast flw traffic at 29 scalar loads dominates the load stream vs 4 vector loads - one input row is reloaded each iteration because the reduction axis (KW=3, IC=3) is fully unrolled inside the KH loop (lines 157, 162) but the OW=8 stride-2 output slab produces only 8 FMA fanout per input-vector load, so the filter weights are re-broadcast for every output column iteration. Additionally, the epilogue (lines 163-234) emits 10 separate vfadd+vmfge+vmerge+vse sequences per output column group - one vector store per OW output, meaning OW is unrolled (factor ~8, lines 192,198,204,210,216,222,228,234) but the clamp/store pattern is serial with no reuse of comparison masks.\",\"improvement_direction\":\"Reduce the per-FMA scalar-broadcast pressure by increasing reuse of loaded filter weights across more output accumulators - i.e., widen the spatial output footprint held in registers so each filter flw amortizes over more vfmacc, or pack filter weights into a vector and use indexed/segment loads instead of 15 scalar flw per inner iteration. Secondarily, reduce the post-loop bias-add/clamp epilogue cost by batching the activation+store pattern so fewer vmfge/vmerge mask-ops are needed per output element.\",\"expected_metric_change\":\"Inner loop FMA-to-scalar-flw ratio should rise above 2:1 (currently ~24/15 inside KH body); total flw count should drop well below 29; vfmacc count may rise modestly while total dynamic instructions fall; epilogue block of 10 clamp-store groups should compress into fewer vector-store sequences.\",\"risk\":\"Medium. CPUConvTileAndDecomposeExpert already produces dense FMA code with LMUL=m1 matching OF=32 exactly (optimal tail-free VL), so any reshaping that forces a generic vectorization path risks losing the specialized im2col-free decomposition. Compile-failure risk is moderate if the new strategy fights the existing tile-and-decompose; regression risk is real since the baseline fills 8 accumulator vregs (v10-v17) cleanly with no spills.\"},\"rank_reason\":\"The single most visible asm inefficiency is the 15 scalar flw broadcasts per inner iteration feeding only 24 FMAs (line 104-135) - this is the dominant dynamic instruction class after the FMAs themselves and directly limits IPC on an in-order RVV core. No spills exist and LMUL=m1 already matches OF=32, so register pressure and vector-width tuning are not the bottleneck; filter-weight reuse is.\"}"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7608,"cache_read_input_tokens":21953,"output_tokens":1254,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7608},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1254,"cache_read_input_tokens":21953,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7608,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7608,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}}